INSERT INTO journal_articles (title, slug, excerpt, content, category, author, tags, is_published, is_featured, read_time_minutes) VALUES
('Apparatus Studio: Sculpting Light and Form', 'apparatus-studio-sculpting-light-form', 'New York-based Apparatus Studio, led by Gabriel Hendifar and Jeremy Anderson, creates sculptural lighting and furniture connecting the historical and cultural through a contemporary lens.', '## Connecting Histories, Crafting Futures

Apparatus Studio, founded by Gabriel Hendifar and Jeremy Anderson in New York, is celebrated for sculptural lighting and furniture. Hendifar, of Iranian descent, infuses cultural depth into work that connects "the historical and cultural through a contemporary lens."

> "At its best, it''s all an act of love." — Gabriel Hendifar

The studio participated in London Design Festival 2024, launched an LA showroom, and is represented by Holly Hunt. Recent collections include the horsehair series.', 'designer_interview', 'Maison Affluency', '{"Apparatus Studio","Gabriel Hendifar","Lighting","New York Design"}', false, false, 3),
('Hervé Van der Straeten: Sculptor of Light and Form', 'herve-van-der-straeten-sculptor-light-form', 'French designer born in 1965, Van der Straeten transitioned from haute couture jewelry to furniture and lighting, mastering bronze to create pieces Christie''s says "transcend all trends."', '## From Haute Couture to Home Couture

Born in 1965, Hervé Van der Straeten began as a jewelry designer for haute couture houses before transitioning to furniture and lighting in bronze. Christie''s notes his furnishings "transcend all trends," with a Feb 2025 sale featuring his work.

His signature pieces — chandeliers, consoles, mirrors in hammered and patinated bronze — are represented on Artsy, 1stDibs, and Incollect.

> His pieces complement collectors'' art without overpowering them.', 'designer_interview', 'Maison Affluency', '{"Hervé Van der Straeten","French Design","Bronze","Sculptural Lighting"}', false, false, 3),
('Éric Schmitt: The Quiet Sculptor of Functional Art', 'eric-schmitt-quiet-sculptor-functional-art', 'French designer whose sculptural forms echo the Romanesque churches of his Poitou childhood. Represented by Carpenters Workshop Gallery and En attendant les Barbares.', '## Silence, Sculpture, and Architecture

> "A piece of furniture needs to exude silence so it can be loved for a long time."

> "My work is the consequence of the sculptor that I almost am, of the architect that I would have liked to have been, and of the designer that I am not quite."

Éric Schmitt''s forms echo the Romanesque churches of his Poitou childhood. He began by forging his own pieces — totems and tables evoking witchcraft. His solo show "Mytho" at Carpenters Workshop Gallery Paris (Sep–Oct 2022) explored archaeology and ancient civilizations. He works in bronze, Bohemian glass, and marble. Also represented by En attendant les Barbares.', 'designer_interview', 'Maison Affluency', '{"Éric Schmitt","French Design","Bronze","Marble","Carpenters Workshop Gallery"}', false, false, 3),
('Jeremy Maxwell Wintrebert: The Alchemist of Glass', 'jeremy-maxwell-wintrebert-alchemist-of-glass', 'French-North American glass artist whose freehand glassblowing earned the 2019 Prix Bettencourt pour l''Intelligence de la Main. Work held by V&A, Palais de Tokyo, and MusVerre.', '## Breathing Life into Glass

Born in Paris, raised in Africa, Jeremy Maxwell Wintrebert established JMW Studio in 2015 beneath the historic Viaduc des Arts in Paris — a street-level atelier chosen so passers-by can watch the craft.

He trained with Dale Chihuly in Seattle and Davide Salvadore in Venice, developing a signature freehand technique using no molds. He won the 2019 Prix Liliane Bettencourt pour l''Intelligence de la Main from Fondation Bettencourt Schueller.

His work is held by the Victoria & Albert Museum, Palais de Tokyo, and MusVerre. Admirers include Pierre Yovanovitch and India Mahdavi (Galerie Magazine). Cloud pendants are among his signature works. Represented by Holly Hunt.', 'designer_interview', 'Maison Affluency', '{"Jeremy Maxwell Wintrebert","Glass Art","Freehand Glassblowing","Bettencourt Prize","JMW Studio"}', false, false, 3),
('Kiko Lopez: Mirrored Reflections from Provence', 'kiko-lopez-mirrored-reflections-provence', 'Puerto Rican-born glass artist based in Provence since 1991, RISD graduate, creating mirrored works from a 19th-century former silkworm farm for over 30 years.', '## The Art of Reflection

Kiko Lopez (b. 1962) is a Puerto Rican artist based in Provence, France since 1991. A graduate of Rhode Island School of Design, he trained as architect and industrial designer before dedicating himself to glass.

Working from a 19th-century former silkworm farm, he creates mirrored glass works using techniques requiring full protective gear due to toxic materials.

> "The design should be generous… In the quality of materials and the timeless purity of form."

Over 30 years of experience. Exhibited at Maison Gerard NYC (first solo NY presentation), Galerie Jacques Lacoste Paris. Represented by Objects With Narratives.', 'designer_interview', 'Maison Affluency', '{"Kiko Lopez","Glass Art","Mirrors","Provence","RISD"}', false, false, 3),
('Noé Duchaufour-Lawrance: Nature''s Curves in Design', 'noe-duchaufour-lawrance-natures-curves', 'French designer known for organic, biomorphic furniture. Collaborated with Saint-Louis crystal on the celebrated Folia collection, as well as Hermès and Ligne Roset.', '## Organic Form, Poetic Function

Noé Duchaufour-Lawrance is a French designer known for his organic, biomorphic approach. He has collaborated with Saint-Louis crystal (Folia collection, 2017 — crystal fused with wood in leaf-shaped forms), Hermès, Ligne Roset, and Bernhardt Design.

He relocated to Portugal during the Covid lockdown (per Suzanne Lovell Inc). NDL Editions is his own publishing label. His Amber Folia Portable Lamp for Cristallerie Saint-Louis showcases his mastery of translucent materials and organic form.', 'designer_interview', 'Maison Affluency', '{"Noé Duchaufour-Lawrance","Organic Design","Saint-Louis Crystal","Folia","NDL Editions"}', false, false, 3),
('Bina Baitel: Crafting Sensory Experiences', 'bina-baitel-crafting-sensory-experiences', 'Franco-Swedish architect who grew up in the Middle East, founded her Paris studio in 2006. Work spans art, design, and architecture with focus on sensory experience.', '## Art, Design, Architecture

Bina Baitel, DPLG Architect, graduated from the National School of Architecture of Paris La Villette. Of Franco-Swedish origin, she grew up in the Middle East, founding her studio in Paris in 2006.

Paris Design Week 2023: she decorated the Château du Tremblay for Christophe Gaillard Gallery. Milan Design Week 2015: OLED Recto-Verso lamp collection. Named "Designer of the Day" by Surface Magazine.

Her focus on sensory design creates contemplative experiences. The studio creates interior and industrial design projects as well as unique creations in collaboration with museums and galleries.', 'designer_interview', 'Maison Affluency', '{"Bina Baitel","French Design","Architecture","Sensory Design","Milan Design Week"}', false, false, 3),
('Pierre Bonnefille: Maître d''Art of Material and Texture', 'pierre-bonnefille-maitre-dart-material-texture', 'Born 1958, Paris-based artist awarded Maître d''Art by the French Ministry of Culture. Creates materials from mineral powder, limestone, lava, and metallic powders.', '## Material as Medium

Pierre Bonnefille (b. 1958, Saint-Quentin) studied at École Boulle and École Nationale des Arts Décoratifs de Paris. Awarded Maître d''Art by the French Ministry of Culture — a title for masters of exceptional craft.

He creates his own materials from mineral powder, limestone, lava, marble, earth, natural pigments and metallic powders. His Bronze Paintings are monumental works where material and color become inseparable.

His collaboration with Olivier Gagnère on the Café Marly at the Musée du Louvre brought international attention. Clients include Christian Liaigre, Hermès, and Cartier (per 1stDibs). Represented by Ateliers Courbet, NYC.', 'designer_interview', 'Maison Affluency', '{"Pierre Bonnefille","Maître d''Art","Bronze Paintings","École Boulle","Café Marly"}', false, false, 3),
('OKHA: The South African Narrative of Refined Living', 'okha-south-african-narrative-refined-living', 'Cape Town-based design studio founded by Adam Courts, creating collectible furniture rooted in craftsmanship, noble materials, and sculptural form.', '## Refined and Personal

OKHA is a furniture design studio based in Cape Town, South Africa, founded by Adam Courts. The studio creates objects that are refined and personal, rooted in craftsmanship, noble materials and sculptural form.

> "How can this curve, this line, this surface, make everyday living feel a little richer?"

Each work is made to last. Featured in House & Garden SA, VISI magazine, SA Decor & Design. International gallery representation. Courts draws on the rich material culture and craft traditions of southern Africa.', 'designer_interview', 'Maison Affluency', '{"OKHA","Adam Courts","South African Design","Collectible Furniture","Cape Town"}', false, false, 3),
('Andy Kerstens: Aesthetic Purity and Artisan Quality', 'andy-kerstens-aesthetic-purity-artisan-quality', 'Antwerp-based designer founded his multidisciplinary studio in 2015. Master of Science in Interior Architecture (cum laude) from University of Antwerp.', '## Architectural Clarity

Andy Kerstens, born in Wilrijk near Antwerp, founded his studio in 2015. He holds a Master of Science in Interior Architecture (cum laude) from the University of Antwerp.

His multidisciplinary practice spans architecture, interior design, and furniture — defined by aesthetic purity, refined proportion and artisan quality. Represented by Galerie Philia.

The studio creates total projects where affinity for craftsmanship, detail, and atmosphere are essential, for residential, catering and retail projects.', 'designer_interview', 'Maison Affluency', '{"Andy Kerstens","Belgian Design","Antwerp","Interior Architecture","Galerie Philia"}', false, false, 3)
